  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThese days hoarding slashings is no longer a viable strategy. Prysm already default their slasher to broadcast by default, and I've been meaning to do the same for Lighthouse for a long time.\r\n\r\nI think we should change the semantics of the `--slasher-broadcast` flag as follows:\r\n\r\n- `<no flag>`: enable broadcast (new default).\r\n- `--slasher-broadcast`: same as present, enable broadcast.\r\n- `--slasher-broadcast=false`: disable broadcast (new argument).\r\n- `--slasher-broadcast=true`: enable broadcast (new argument).\r\n\r\nI think this can be achieved using `clap`'s `.default()` method.\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\n- [x] Modify the CLI parsing logic for `--slasher-broadcast`\r\n- [x] Add/adjust tests for the 4 configurations of flags described above\r\n",
